1. Ti *kažeš* da ti se ne sviđa ova pesma. (You *say* that you don't like this song.)
2. Kada mi *kažeš* da si spreman, pozvaću te. (When you *tell* me you're ready, I'll call you.)
3. Oni *kažu* da je jučerašnja utakmica bila sjajna. (They *say* that yesterday's game was great.)
4. Da li bi mi *rekao* kada si se vratio kući sinoć? (Would you *tell* me when you got back home last night?)
5. Kada bismo mogli da *kažemo* da smo uspeli u svemu što smo zamislili? (When could we *say* that we've succeeded in everything we've imagined?)
6. *Kažeš* da si mi poslao mejl, ali nisam ga dobio. (You *say* you sent me an email, but I didn't receive it.)
7. Oni će mi *reći* ko je pobedio na izborima. (They will *tell* me who won the elections.)
8. Molim te, *kaži* mi šta ti smeta. (Please, *tell* me what bothers you.)
9. Kada si *rekao* da ćeš doći, nisam očekivao da ćeš biti toliko kasno. (When you *said* you were coming, I didn't expect you to be so late.)
10. Niko ne želi da *kaže* istinu, jer je boje da će biti kažnjen. (Nobody wants to *say* the truth because they're afraid of being punished.)